			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=121232">Firiona Vie</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Dragonscale Quest for a Warrior only Weapon</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Dragonscale Quest for a Warrior only Weapon</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=138625"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:bosspgp@monmouth.com">Belric</a> | 
		                        5/22/2000 4:22:32 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Talk to Squire Fuzzmin(hailing him gets some dialog but he keeps moving)<BR>
<BR>
1. 'What quest is Sir Hobble on?'<BR>
-- Squire Fuzzmin says 'Sir Hobble is searching for [three special dragons]. For all I know they are not even dragons. He can't see or hear very well. He still thinks I am the only troll squire around.<BR>
<BR>
2.'What three special dragons?' <BR>
-- Squire Fuzzmin says 'Apparently he is after three dragons which are supposedly named Azdalin, Gylton and Xyfl. He will not rest until he holds their scales. I wish you could [find the dragons].<BR>
<BR>
3.'I will find the dragons' <BR>
-- Squire Fuzzmin says 'If you bring me the three scales I will be able to place them upon the next three victims of Sir Hobbles. Then we can depart from this accursed isle. He would never know the difference. Do this and I will give you a warrior weapon out of the old knights armory. <BR>
These wurms are in the Burning Woods.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
OK here is what I have heard. I am sorry that I can not state fact. I have 2 of the 3 scales and plan to find out soon.<BR>
The weapon is called Dragonslayer.<BR>
Dmg 30 Del 40 + 10 STR and casts a fire base spell. No drop and Warrior only!<BR>
I have no info on this proc. <BR>
I have heard that it might be a flaming sword.<BR>
Fact now:<BR>
The Squire runs out of FV and over to the East side of the zone. There he meets his master. The two of them then go on killing mobbs.<BR>
The Squire doesnt stop for hails.(Opinion now starting hehe) The best time to get him is when him and his master are killing something. <BR>
I have payed about 3kpp per scale. I believe them to be worth this amount. I have offered more for Xyfl's scale. It seems he might be more rare then the other two. I believe this to be because no one hunts in the area he spawns in. I believe he spawns in the NE corner near Chardok. Any info on his spawn loc would help. As for the other two they seem to pass by the Giant fort. Good Luck and Good Hunting. <BR>
I would like to thank Swiftlion  who posted on the burning woods page.  Without his info I would have never known about this.
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
