	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ya need instructions on how to turn-in the scales?  I've now done the turn-in 7 times, and have it down to an art.  Here's how you do it:<BR>
<BR>
Need 2 people minimum:  A tracker (druid/ranger) and a mem wiper (cleric/chanter -- note I'll call them the cleric during the instructions).  Either of them can hold the scales, or even someone else with them.  Adding trackers speeds up the process.<BR>
<BR>
1.  Assemble on the bridge to FV (or near it if KOS).  Everyone gets a fresh sow.<BR>
<BR>
2.  Cleric goes to the little tavern in the NW corner of FV.  It's the one with the female barbarian and the male ogre.  Hail the female barbarian and you will see the trigger phrase &quot;i want to see something interesting&quot;.  Spam her with the trigger phrase about 20 times (overkill, but seems to speed things up).<BR>
<BR>
3.  Say &quot;triggered&quot; to the group.  The tracker then runs NE from the bridge and begins searching for Sir Hobble.  Sir Hobble is usually moving West slowly at this point, but it varies, so you may have to look around a bit.  This is where Rangers have a definate advantage since their tracking is better.<BR>
<BR>
4.  When the tracker finds Sir Hobble, spam him with Hails until he talks of the Bear (20 doesn't hurt).  This causes Squire Fuzzmin to spawn.<BR>
<BR>
5.  The Squire makes a B-Line to Sir Hobble.  After triggering Sir Hobble, tracker calls out LOCs as hobble continues to move.  The rest of the group on the bridge (and especially the cleric) head to him.  It sometimes takes a full 5 minutes for the Squire to get to Hobble.<BR>
<BR>
6.  Once the Squire gets to Hobble (or earlier if you can catch him en route) the cleric should Root him.  This will aggro him, so back up and use Atone (or chanter mem blank spell).  Remember Atone sometimes doesn't work the first time.  Start hailing Fuzzmin.  If you get him to talk, then he is no longer aggroed (but still rooted).  <BR>
<BR>
7.  One at a time, give him the 3 scales.  Enjoy your wurmslayer.  If you have a lot of people, or root breaks early, just re-root him and re-atone him.  If Sir Hobble aggroes anytime during this, just pull him away from Fuzzmin and root him and ignore him.  Atone him if you want, but it isn't necessary.<BR>
<BR>
Good luck!<BR>
<BR>
Josiefuz<BR>
53 Rezmaster of Sol Ro
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
